{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Escalation quote: \"scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content\". This failure is most likely at a module handoff boundary (diff extraction -> review-input builder), where one module may correctly parse hunks but another may accidentally rehydrate full files. REAL-INFRA/LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP checks: no real OS/network/subprocess required, no dependence on model judgment, no multi-agentic chain.","test_description":"Wire the real diff parser and prompt/input-construction modules together with a fixture PR diff containing both changed and unchanged regions; assert the produced review payload includes only changed hunks and excludes unchanged file content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.4,"Integration":0.5,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Escalation quote: \"attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request\". Correctness depends on real GitHub diff-position semantics and server-side validation of line/path/side/commit context; mocked APIs can accept invalid mappings that real PR UI/API rejects or renders incorrectly (MOCK-HIDE). Rejected lower level: Integration is disqualified because behavior explicitly targets real PR diff positioning behavior.","test_description":"Against a real test PR, post inline comments using computed positions from the automation and verify via GitHub API/UI metadata that each comment lands on the intended file/hunk/line in the diff view.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Escalation quote: \"identifies at least one real defect\". This is model-decision quality, not wrapper plumbing; stubs always hide misses/failure to detect the bug (LLM-DEP). Rejected higher level: Workflow is not required by this behavior text because it only requires one successful defect-identification outcome, not correctness of multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Run the real model on a benchmark PR containing a seeded known bug; assert at least one returned finding correctly points to that bug (allowing wording variation but requiring semantic match).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to a posted inline comment ID from the same run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Escalation quote: \"corresponds to a posted inline comment ID from the same run\". This is cross-module state consistency (inline post results -> summary assembler). Rejected higher levels: System disqualified because real network/OS behavior is not required to catch ID-linkage bugs; Agentic disqualified because mapping correctness does not depend on model output quality.","test_description":"Execute the posting and summary-construction pipeline in-process using deterministic finding fixtures and simulated successful inline post responses; assert each summary item references an inline comment ID emitted in that exact run context.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"No inline finding is dropped from the final summary payload before posting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Escalation quote: \"No inline finding is dropped from the final summary payload\". This targets handoff integrity across local modules (finding collector -> summary payload builder). Rejected higher levels: System is disqualified since drop/omission bugs can be caught without real HTTP/OS; Agentic is disqualified because this behavior is about preservation of items, not quality of model judgments.","test_description":"Run aggregation and summary-payload generation with a fixture set of inline findings (including edge cases like duplicates and ordering); assert payload cardinality/content preserves all expected findings before post call.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The automation sequence (read diff, post inline comments, post summary) succeeds for a real pull request when provided a fixed precomputed finding set.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Escalation quote: \"succeeds for a real pull request\" and explicit sequence over real operations. This requires real HTTP/API behavior, auth, rate limits, and PR state interactions; mocks can hide transport/protocol failures (REAL-INFRA, MOCK-HIDE). Rejected higher level: Agentic is disqualified by \"fixed precomputed finding set\" (no dependence on live model decisions).","test_description":"Run the automation end-to-end against a real test PR using a fixed finding fixture (no live model generation), and assert successful diff read, inline comment creation, and summary comment creation with expected artifacts.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.82,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The full live run with model-generated findings (read diff, analyze, post inline comments, post summary) completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Escalation quote: \"full live run with model-generated findings\" and the explicit chained sequence \"read diff, analyze, post inline comments, post summary\". This is a full agent pipeline with at least one real model decision plus downstream stages that must remain coherent end-to-end; lower-level tests miss cross-stage failure propagation.","test_description":"Execute unattended end-to-end on a real PR with live model analysis enabled; verify the run completes, produced findings are posted inline, and summary is posted with consistent references to the created inline comments.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.32,"Workflow":0.58}}]}
